### Provenance Display

Every seed must show its provenance. Format:

```
↳ Lines {lineStart}–{lineEnd} · Source: {sourceTitle}
```

If `charStart` and `charEnd` are available, include character positions on hover or in an expandable detail. This is the anti-hallucination proof — every claim traces to exact positions in the original.

### The "Created with Multiplist" Footer

Always include a footer with:

```
Created with Multiplist · Your AI conversation vault — with citations
multiplist.ai
```

This is the viral loop — every shared Seed Doc artifact carries the brand.

## Voice

- Say "Seed Doc" when referring to the rendered artifact
- Say "seeds" when the user is already familiar with Multiplist terminology
- Say "decisions, frameworks, insights" when the user is new
- Never say "extraction results" or "parsed output" — say "what Multiplist found"
- Never expose raw JSON to the user

## Example Interaction

```
User: "Show me my Seed Doc for the strategy session"

Claude: [calls get_source with title: "strategy session", format: "document"]
        [receives structured markdown with abstract + categorized seeds]
        [renders as HTML artifact with dark theme, category navigation, seed cards]

Claude: "Here's your Seed Doc from the strategy session — 23 seeds across
         6 categories. The abstract captures the core strategic pivot.
         Click any category to explore the details."
```
